-- Turkey's Halkbank to Start Offering Pensions Through Life-Insurance Unit
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2010-12-08T06:33:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/turkey-s-halkbank-to-start-offering-pensions-through-life-insurance-unit.html
Turkiye Halk Bankasi AS, a Turkish
state-run bank, said its life insurer unit Birlik Hayat Sigorta
AS will start offering pensions.  The unit will also change its name to Halk Hayat &
Emeklilik AS, Halkbank said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock
Exchange yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Aydan Eksin at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net  